738    @staticmethod
739    def _step7(
740        OS: OSType,
741        ap_state_pointers: APStatePointers,
742        sorts: Sorts,
743        bindings: Bindings,
744        statics: Statics,
745        debug: bool = False,
746        viz: bool = False,
747    ) -> Tuple[Set[LearnedLiftedFluent], Set[LearnedLiftedAction]]:
748        """Step 7: Formation of PDDL action schema
749        Implicitly includes Step 6 (statics) by including statics as an argument
750        and adding to the relevant actions while being constructed.
751        """
752
753        # delete zero-object if it's state machine was discarded
754        if not OS[0]:
755            del OS[0]
756            del ap_state_pointers[0]
757
758        # all_aps = {action_name: [AP]}
759        all_aps: Dict[str, List[AP]] = defaultdict(list)
760        for aps in ap_state_pointers.values():
761            for ap in aps:
762                all_aps[ap.action.name].append(ap)
763
764        state_params = defaultdict(dict)
765        state_params_to_hyps = defaultdict(dict)
766        for sort in bindings:
767            state_params[sort] = defaultdict(dict)
768            state_params_to_hyps[sort] = defaultdict(dict)
769            for state in bindings[sort]:
770                keys = {b.param for b in bindings[sort][state]}
771                typ = None
772                for key in keys:
773                    hyps = [
774                        b.hypothesis for b in bindings[sort][state] if b.param == key
775                    ]
776                    # assert that all are the same G_
777                    assert len(set([h.G_ for h in hyps])) == 1
778                    state_params[sort][state][key] = hyps[0].G_
779                    state_params_to_hyps[sort][state][key] = hyps
780
781        if viz:
782            LOCM._debug_state_machines(OS, ap_state_pointers, state_params)
783
784        fluents = defaultdict(dict)
785        actions = {}
786        for sort in ap_state_pointers:
787            sort_str = f"sort{sort}"
788            for ap in ap_state_pointers[sort]:
789                if ap.action.name not in actions:
790                    actions[ap.action.name] = LearnedLiftedAction(
791                        ap.action.name,
792                        [None for _ in range(len(all_aps[ap.action.name]))],  # type: ignore
793                    )
794                a = actions[ap.action.name]
795                a.param_sorts[ap.pos - 1] = sort_str
796
797                start_pointer, end_pointer = ap_state_pointers[sort][ap]
798                start_state, end_state = LOCM._pointer_to_set(
799                    OS[sort], start_pointer, end_pointer
800                )
801
802                start_fluent_name = f"sort{sort}_state{start_state}"
803                if start_fluent_name not in fluents[ap.action.name]:
804                    start_fluent = LearnedLiftedFluent(
805                        start_fluent_name,
806                        param_sorts=[sort_str],
807                        param_act_inds=[ap.pos - 1],
808                    )
809                    fluents[ap.action.name][start_fluent_name] = start_fluent
810
811                start_fluent = fluents[ap.action.name][start_fluent_name]
812
813                if (
814                    sort in state_params_to_hyps
815                    and start_state in state_params_to_hyps[sort]
816                ):
817                    for param in state_params_to_hyps[sort][start_state]:
818                        psort = None
819                        pind = None
820                        for hyp in state_params_to_hyps[sort][start_state][param]:
821                            if hyp.C == ap:
822                                if (psort is not None and psort != hyp.G_) or \
823                                   (pind is not None and pind != hyp.l_):
824                                    print(f"\n\tError: The following set of hypotheses for sort {sort} and state {start_state} are not consistent (ap = {ap}):")
825                                    for hyp in state_params_to_hyps[sort][start_state][param]:
826                                        if hyp.C == ap:
827                                            print(f"\t\t{hyp}")
828                                    print("\n\t This domain cannot be handled by LOCMv1. Please see https://github.com/AI-Planning/macq/discussions/200 for more info.\n\n")
829                                    exit(1)
830                                assert psort is None or psort == hyp.G_
831                                assert pind is None or pind == hyp.l_
832                                psort = hyp.G_
833                                pind = hyp.l_
834                        if psort is not None:
835                            start_fluent.param_sorts.append(f"sort{psort}")
836                            start_fluent.param_act_inds.append(pind - 1)
837
838                a.update_precond(start_fluent)
839
840                if end_state != start_state:
841                    end_fluent_name = f"sort{sort}_state{end_state}"
842                    if end_fluent_name not in fluents[ap.action.name]:
843                        end_fluent = LearnedLiftedFluent(
844                            end_fluent_name,
845                            param_sorts=[sort_str],
846                            param_act_inds=[ap.pos - 1],
847                        )
848                        fluents[ap.action.name][end_fluent_name] = end_fluent
849
850                    end_fluent = fluents[ap.action.name][end_fluent_name]
851
852                    if (
853                        sort in state_params_to_hyps
854                        and end_state in state_params_to_hyps[sort]
855                    ):
856                        for param in state_params_to_hyps[sort][end_state]:
857                            psort = None
858                            pind = None
859                            for hyp in state_params_to_hyps[sort][end_state][param]:
860                                if hyp.B == ap:
861                                    if (psort is not None and psort != hyp.G_) or \
862                                       (pind is not None and pind != hyp.k_):
863                                         print(f"\n\tError: The following set of hypotheses for sort {sort} and state {end_state} are not consistent (ap = {ap}):")
864                                         for hyp in state_params_to_hyps[sort][end_state][param]:
865                                              if hyp.B == ap:
866                                                    print(f"\t\t{hyp}")
867                                         print("\n\t This domain cannot be handled by LOCMv1. Please see https://github.com/AI-Planning/macq/discussions/200 for more info.\n\n")
868                                         exit(1)
869                                    assert psort is None or psort == hyp.G_
870                                    assert pind is None or pind == hyp.k_
871                                    psort = hyp.G_
872                                    pind = hyp.k_
873                            if psort is not None:
874                                end_fluent.param_sorts.append(f"sort{psort}")
875                                end_fluent.param_act_inds.append(pind - 1)
876
877                    a.update_delete(start_fluent)
878                    a.update_add(end_fluent)
879
880        # Step 6: Extraction of static preconditions
881        for action in actions.values():
882            if action.name in statics:
883                for static in statics[action.name]:
884                    action.update_precond(static)
885
886        return set(
887            fluent
888            for action_fluents in fluents.values()
889            for fluent in action_fluents.values()
890        ), set(actions.values())

LOCM

LOCM( obs_tracelist: macq.observation.observed_tracelist.ObservedTraceList, statics: Union[Dict[str, List[str]], NoneType] = None, viz: bool = False, view: bool = False, debug: Union[bool, Dict[str, bool], List[str]] = False) 
188    def __new__(
189        cls,
190        obs_tracelist: ObservedTraceList,
191        statics: Optional[Statics] = None,
192        viz: bool = False,
193        view: bool = False,
194        debug: Union[bool, Dict[str, bool], List[str]] = False,
195    ):
196        """Creates a new Model object.
197        Args:
198            observations (ObservationList):
199                The state observations to extract the model from.
200            statics (Dict[str, List[str]]):
201                A dictionary mapping an action name and its arguments to the
202                list of static preconditions of the action. A precondition should
203                be a tuple, where the first element is the predicate name and the
204                rest correspond to the arguments of the action (1-indexed).
205                E.g. static( next(C1, C2), put_on_card_in_homecell(C2, C1, _) )
206                should is provided as: {"put_on_card_in_homecell": [("next", 2, 1)]}
207            viz (bool):
208                Whether to visualize the FSM.
209            view (bool):
210                Whether to view the FSM visualization.
211
212        Raises:
213            IncompatibleObservationToken:
214                Raised if the observations are not identity observation.
215        """
216        if obs_tracelist.type is not ActionObservation:
217            raise IncompatibleObservationToken(obs_tracelist.type, LOCM)
218
219        if len(obs_tracelist) != 1:
220            warn("LOCM only supports a single trace, using first trace only")
221
222        if isinstance(debug, bool) and debug:
223            debug = defaultdict(lambda: True)
224        elif isinstance(debug, dict):
225            debug = defaultdict(lambda: False, debug)
226        elif isinstance(debug, list):
227            debug = defaultdict(lambda: False, {k: True for k in debug})
228        else:
229            debug = defaultdict(lambda: False)
230
231        obs_trace = obs_tracelist[0]
232        fluents, actions = None, None
233
234        sorts = LOCM._get_sorts(obs_trace, debug=debug["get_sorts"])
235
236        if debug["sorts"]:
237            sortid2objs = {v: [] for v in set(sorts.values())}
238            for k, v in sorts.items():
239                sortid2objs[v].append(k)
240            print("\nSorts:\n")
241            pprint(sortid2objs)
242            print("\n")
243
244        TS, ap_state_pointers, OS = LOCM._step1(obs_trace, sorts, debug["step1"])
245        HS = LOCM._step3(TS, ap_state_pointers, OS, sorts, debug["step3"])
246        bindings = LOCM._step4(HS, debug["step4"])
247        bindings = LOCM._step5(HS, bindings, debug["step5"])
248        fluents, actions = LOCM._step7(
249            OS,
250            ap_state_pointers,
251            sorts,
252            bindings,
253            statics if statics is not None else {},
254            debug["step7"],
255            viz,
256        )
257
258        return Model(fluents, actions)

class SLAF: 
 16class SLAF:
 17    """SLAF model extraction method.
 18
 19    Amir, E, and A Chang. 2008. “Learning Partially Observable Deterministic Action Models.”
 20    Journal of Artificial Intelligence Research 33: 349–402. https://doi.org/10.1613/jair.2575.
 21
 22    Extracts a Model from state observations using the SLAF technique. The AS-STRIPS-SLAF
 23    algorithm is used to extract the effects of actions given a trace/observation. The algorithm
 24    is incapable of finding the preconditions of those actions, however.
 25
 26    Note that SLAF learns partially observable, deterministic action models, and thus takes
 27    PartialObservation as the token type.
 28
 29    The AS-STRIPS-SLAF algorithm works by defining "action propositions" for each action that define
 30    the possible preconditions, effects, or lack-thereof of that action and every possible fluent. A
 31    propositional formula is updated as each step is iterated through, and kept in a "fluent-factored form"
 32    that specifies the possible "explanations" behind each fluent being true, false, or unaffected. As actions
 33    are taken and states observed, these reasonings are updated and simplified. (Note that the pieces of the formula
 34    are stored carefully so as to easily conjoin them into one CNF formula later). Once all steps in the trace
 35    have been iterated through, the CNF formula is created, and all possible fluents/action propositions are
 36    iterated through to determine which ones are entailed. This information is then used to extract the Model.
 37    """
 38
 39    # only need one true and one false
 40    top = true
 41    bottom = false
 42
 43    def __new__(cls, o_list: ObservedTraceList, debug: bool = False, sample: bool = False):
 44        """Creates a new Model object.
 45
 46        Args:
 47            o_list (ObservationList):
 48                The state observations to extract the model from.
 49            debug_mode (bool):
 50                An optional mode that helps the user track any fluents they desire by examining the evolution
 51                of their fluent-factored formulas through the steps.
 52            sample (bool):
 53                An optional mode that allows the user to sample the possible models instead of returning
 54                one that includes only guaranteed entailed fluents.
 55        Raises:
 56            IncompatibleObservationToken:
 57                Raised if the observations are not identity observation.
 58        """
 59        if o_list.type is not AtomicPartialObservation:
 60            raise IncompatibleObservationToken(o_list.type, SLAF)
 61
 62        if len(o_list) != 1:
 63            raise Exception("The SLAF extraction technique only takes one trace.")
 64
 65        SLAF.debug_mode = debug
 66        entailed = SLAF.__as_strips_slaf(o_list, sample)
 67        # return the Model
 68        return SLAF.__sort_results(o_list, entailed)
 69
 70    @staticmethod
 71    def __get_initial_fluent_factored(o_list: ObservedTraceList):
 72        """Gets the initial fluent-factored formula of an observation/trace.
 73
 74        Args:
 75            o_list (ObservationList):
 76                The observation list to extract the fluent-factored formula from.
 77
 78        Returns:
 79            A list of dictionaries that holds the fluent-factored formula.
 80        """
 81        top = SLAF.top
 82        bottom = SLAF.bottom
 83        fluents = set()
 84        # get all the base fluents
 85        fluents.update([f for obs in o_list for token in obs for f in token.state])
 86
 87        # set up the initial fluent factored form for the problem
 88        raw_fluent_factored = {}
 89        for f in fluents:
 90            phi = {}
 91            phi["fluent"] = Var(f)
 92            phi["pos expl"] = {top}
 93            phi["neg expl"] = {top}
 94            phi["neutral"] = {top}
 95            raw_fluent_factored[f] = phi
 96        return raw_fluent_factored
 97
 98    @staticmethod
 99    def __remove_subsumed_clauses(phi_form: Set):
100        """Removes subsumed clauses to simplify the given formula.
101        This is step 2. of AS-STRIPS-SLAF, however this step was taken as the formula was
102        progressively created instead of once at the end, for efficiency purposes.
103
104        Args:
105            phi_form (Set):
106                The set (conjunction) of formulas to simplify.
107        """
108        to_del = set()
109        # if the overall phi formula (conjunction) has false, throw everything out
110        if false in phi_form:
111            phi_form.clear()
112            return
113        # eliminate subsumed clauses by comparing each formula with the others
114        for f in phi_form:
115            for other in phi_form:
116                # simplify the formulas to sets of strings for comparison purposes
117                if isinstance(f, Or) or isinstance(f, And):
118                    f_set = {str(o) for o in f.children}
119                else:
120                    f_set = {str(f)}
121                if not isinstance(other, Var):
122                    other_set = {str(o) for o in other.children}
123                    # if the subformula is a conjunction and has false in it, throw it out
124                    if isinstance(other, And):
125                        if "false" in other_set:
126                            to_del.add(other)
127                            break
128                    # if the subformula is a disjunction and has true in it, throw it out
129                    elif isinstance(other, Or):
130                        if "true" in other_set:
131                            to_del.add(other)
132                            break
133                    # otherwise, if the subformula can be represented by a smaller subformula, throw it out.
134                    # also, "true" and "false" are empty sets, and unless we have one of the two cases above, we need to
135                    # prevent them from throwing out formulas unnecessarily
136                    if (
137                        f_set.issubset(other_set)
138                        and f_set != other_set
139                        and f != true
140                        and f != false
141                    ):
142                        to_del.add(other)
143        # discard unnecessary formulas
144        for t in to_del:
145            phi_form.discard(t)
146
147    @staticmethod
148    def __or_refactor(maybe_lit: Union[Or, Var]):
149        """Converts a "Var" fluent to an "Or" fluent.
150
151        Args:
152            maybe_lit (Union[Or, Var]):
153                Fluent that is either type "Or" or "Var."
154
155        Returns:
156            A corresponding fluent of type "Or."
157        """
158        return Or([maybe_lit]) if isinstance(maybe_lit, Var) else maybe_lit
159
160    @staticmethod
161    def __sort_results(observations: ObservedTraceList, entailed: Set):
162        """Generates a `Model` given the set of entailed propositions.
163
164        Args:
165            observations (ObservationLists):
166                The observations supplied for extraction.
167            entailed (Set)
168                The set of propositions that were found to be entailed.
169
170        Returns:
171            The extracted `Model`.
172        """
173        learned_actions = {}
174        model_fluents = observations.get_fluents()
175
176        # iterate through each step
177        for o in observations:
178            for token in o:
179                # if an action was taken on this step
180                if token.action:
181                    # set up a base LearnedAction with the known information
182                    learned_actions[str(token.action)] = extract.LearnedAction(
183                        token.action.name,
184                        token.action.obj_params,
185                        cost=token.action.cost,
186                    )
187        # iterate through all entailed propositions
188        for e in entailed:
189            precond = " is a precondition of "
190            effect = " causes "
191            neutral = " has no effect on "
192            e = str(e)
193            # if this proposition holds information about a precondition
194            if precond in e:
195                # split to separate precondition and action, get rid of extra brackets
196                info_split = e[1:-1].split(precond)
197                precond = info_split[0]
198                action = info_split[1]
199                # update the precondition of this action with the appropriate fluent
200                #  only if it's a positive precondition
201                if "~" not in precond:
202                    learned_actions[action].update_precond({precond})
203            # if this proposition holds information about an effect
204            elif effect in e:
205                # split to separate effect and action, get rid of extra brackets
206                info_split = e[1:-1].split(effect)
207                action = info_split[0]
208                effect = info_split[1]
209                # update either add or delete effects appropriately
210                if "~" in effect:
211                    # get rid of "~"
212                    effect = effect[1:]
213                    # update the delete effects of this action with the appropriate fluent
214                    learned_actions[action].update_delete({effect})
215                else:
216                    # update the add effects of this action with the appropriate fluent
217                    learned_actions[action].update_add({effect})
218        return Model(model_fluents, set(learned_actions.values()))
219
220    @staticmethod
221    def __as_strips_slaf(o_list: ObservedTraceList, sample: bool):
222        """Implements the AS-STRIPS-SLAF algorithm from section 5.3 of the SLAF paper.
223        Iterates through the action/observation pairs of each observation/trace, returning
224        a fluent-factored transition belief formula that filters according to that action/observation.
225        The transition belief formulas for each trace/observation are conjoined to get one final formula,
226        which is then solved using a SAT solver to extract models.
227
228        Args:
229            o_list (ObservationList):
230                The list of observations/traces to apply the filtering algorithm to.
231                NOTE: with the current implementation, SLAF only works with a single trace.
232
233            sample (bool):
234                If true, an arbitrary solution will be produced rather than just the entailed literals.
235
236        Returns:
237            The set of fluents that are entailed.
238        """
239
240        global e
241        top = SLAF.top
242        bottom = SLAF.bottom
243        validity_constraints = set()
244        all_var = set()
245        debug_mode = SLAF.debug_mode
246
247        # get the fluent factored formula
248        raw_fluent_factored = SLAF.__get_initial_fluent_factored(o_list)
249        # get all base fluents to check entailments later
250        all_var.update([phi["fluent"] for phi in raw_fluent_factored.values()])
251        # iterate through every observation
252        for obs in o_list:
253            # more options if the user is in debug mode
254            if debug_mode:
255                all_f_details = [f["fluent"].name for f in raw_fluent_factored.values()]
256                all_f_details.sort()
257                for f in all_f_details:
258                    print(f)
259                to_obs = []
260                user_input = ""
261                while user_input != "x":
262                    user_input = input(
263                        "Which fluents do you want to observe? Enter 'x' when you are finished.\n"
264                    )
265                    if user_input in all_f_details:
266                        to_obs.append(user_input)
267                        print(user_input + " added to the debugging list.")
268                    else:
269                        if user_input != "x":
270                            print("The fluent you entered is invalid.")
271
272            # iterate through all tokens (action/observation pairs) in this observation/trace
273            for token in obs:
274                if debug_mode:
275                    print("-" * 100)
276
277                all_o = []
278                # retrieve list of observations from the current state. Missing fluents are not taken into account.
279                for f in token.state:
280                    if token.state[f] != None:
281                        all_o.append(str(Var(f, token.state[f])))
282
283                """Steps 1 (d)-(e) of AS-STRIPS-SLAF are taken care of in this loop.
284                Note that steps (d)-(e) are done first as the action-observation order of SLAF is opposite to that of
285                how steps are stored in macq.
286
287                Iterate through every fluent in the fluent-factored transition belief formula and take
288                account of all of the current observations BEFORE the next action is taken."""
289                for phi in raw_fluent_factored.values():
290                    f = phi["fluent"]
291                    if str(f) in all_o:
292                        """Step 1 (d): If this fluent is observed, update the formula accordingly.
293                        Since we know the fluent is now true, the prior possible explanation for the fluent being true
294                        (involving past actions, etc) are now set to the neutral explanation; that is, one of those explanations
295                        has to be true in order for the prior action to have no effect on the fluent currently being true.
296                        """
297                        phi["neutral"].update([p.simplify() for p in phi["pos expl"]])
298                        phi["pos expl"] = {top}
299                        phi["neg expl"] = {bottom}
300                        if debug_mode and str(f) in to_obs:
301                            print(
302                                f"{f} was observed to be true after the previous action was taken."
303                            )
304
305                    elif str(~f) in all_o:
306                        """For Step 1 (e), the opposite happens if the fluent is observed to be false."""
307                        phi["neutral"].update([n.simplify() for n in phi["neg expl"]])
308                        phi["pos expl"] = {bottom}
309                        phi["neg expl"] = {top}
310                        if debug_mode and str(f) in to_obs:
311                            print(
312                                f"{f} was observed to be false after the previous action was taken."
313                            )
314                    """If the fluent is not observed to be either true or false (it is missing), then nothing happens."""
315                # display current updates
316                if debug_mode:
317                    print("Update according to observations.")
318                    for obj in to_obs:
319                        f_str = raw_fluent_factored[obj]["fluent"].name
320                        phi = raw_fluent_factored[f_str]
321                        print("\nfluent: " + f_str)
322                        print("\npossible expl. for fluent being true:")
323                        for f in phi["pos expl"]:
324                            if f == top:
325                                print("true")
326                            elif f == bottom:
327                                print("false")
328                            else:
329                                e.pprint(f)
330                        print("\npossible expl. for fluent being false:")
331                        for f in phi["neg expl"]:
332                            if f == top:
333                                print("true")
334                            elif f == bottom:
335                                print("false")
336                            else:
337                                e.pprint(f)
338                        print("\npossible expl. for fluent being unaffected:")
339                        for f in phi["neutral"]:
340                            if f == top:
341                                print("true")
342                            elif f == bottom:
343                                print("false")
344                            else:
345                                e.pprint(f)
346                    print()
347
348                """Steps 1. (a)-(c) and Step 2 of AS-STRIPS-SLAF are taken care of in this loop."""
349                a = token.action
350                # ensures that the action is not None (happens on the last step of a trace)
351                if a:
352                    # iterate through every fluent in the fluent-factored transition belief formula
353                    for phi in raw_fluent_factored.values():
354                        f = phi["fluent"]
355
356                        # create action propositions
357                        pos_precond = Var(f"({f} is a precondition of {a})")
358                        neg_precond = Var(f"(~{f} is a precondition of {a})")
359                        pos_effect = Var(f"({a} causes {f})")
360                        neg_effect = Var(f"({a} causes ~{f})")
361                        neutral = Var(f"({a} has no effect on {f})")
362
363                        all_var.update(
364                            [pos_precond, neg_precond, pos_effect, neg_effect, neutral]
365                        )
366
367                        # update the fluent-factored formula
368                        all_phi_pos = [p.simplify() for p in phi["pos expl"]]
369                        all_phi_neg = [n.simplify() for n in phi["neg expl"]]
370                        all_phi_neut = [n.simplify() for n in phi["neutral"]]
371                        phi["pos expl"] = set()
372                        phi["neg expl"] = set()
373
374                        """Steps 1 (a-c) - Update every fluent in the fluent-factored transition belief formula
375                        with information from the last step."""
376
377                        """Step 1 (a) - update the neutral effects."""
378                        phi["neutral"].update(
379                            [(~pos_precond | p).simplify() for p in all_phi_pos]
380                        )
381                        phi["neutral"].update(
382                            [(~neg_precond | n).simplify() for n in all_phi_neg]
383                        )
384
385                        """Step 1 (b) - update the positive effects."""
386                        phi["pos expl"].add(pos_effect | neutral)
387                        phi["pos expl"].add(pos_effect | ~neg_precond)
388                        phi["pos expl"].update(
389                            [(pos_effect | p).simplify() for p in all_phi_pos]
390                        )
391
392                        """Step 1 (c) - update the negative effects."""
393                        phi["neg expl"].add(neg_effect | neutral)
394                        phi["neg expl"].add(neg_effect | ~pos_precond)
395                        phi["neg expl"].update(
396                            [(neg_effect | n).simplify() for n in all_phi_neg]
397                        )
398
399                        """add validity constraints (from section 5.2 of the SLAF paper)."""
400                        validity_constraints.add(pos_effect | neg_effect | neutral)
401                        validity_constraints.add((~pos_effect | ~neg_effect))
402                        validity_constraints.add(~neg_effect | ~neutral)
403                        validity_constraints.add(~pos_effect | ~neutral)
404                        validity_constraints.add(~pos_precond | ~neg_precond)
405
406                        """Step 2 - eliminate subsumed clauses in phi."""
407                        SLAF.__remove_subsumed_clauses(phi["pos expl"])
408                        SLAF.__remove_subsumed_clauses(phi["neg expl"])
409                        SLAF.__remove_subsumed_clauses(phi["neutral"])
410                # display current updates
411                if debug_mode:
412                    if a:
413                        print("\nAction taken: " + str(a) + "\n")
414                        for obj in to_obs:
415                            f_str = raw_fluent_factored[obj]["fluent"].name
416                            phi = raw_fluent_factored[f_str]
417                            print("\nfluent: " + f_str)
418                            print(
419                                "\npossible expl. for fluent being true after "
420                                + str(a)
421                                + ":"
422                            )
423                            for f in phi["pos expl"]:
424                                if f == top:
425                                    print("true")
426                                elif f == bottom:
427                                    print("false")
428                                else:
429                                    e.pprint(f)
430                            print(
431                                "\npossible expl. for fluent being false after "
432                                + str(a)
433                                + ":"
434                            )
435                            for f in phi["neg expl"]:
436                                if f == top:
437                                    print("true")
438                                elif f == bottom:
439                                    print("false")
440                                else:
441                                    e.pprint(f)
442                            print(
443                                "\npossible expl. for fluent being unaffected after "
444                                + str(a)
445                                + ":"
446                            )
447                            for f in phi["neutral"]:
448                                if f == top:
449                                    print("true")
450                                elif f == bottom:
451                                    print("false")
452                                else:
453                                    e.pprint(f)
454                    print()
455                    user_input = input("Hit enter to continue.\n")
456
457        formula = set()
458        """Convert to formula once you have stepped through all observations and applied all transformations.
459        NOTE: This would have to be refactored if the functionality for multiple traces was added, as each trace would
460        have to store its own separate formulas, and the conjunction would be taken at the end."""
461        for phi in raw_fluent_factored.values():
462            f = phi["fluent"]
463            # convert to formula for each fluent
464            all_phi_pos = [p.simplify() for p in phi["pos expl"]]
465            all_phi_neg = [n.simplify() for n in phi["neg expl"]]
466            all_phi_neut = [n.simplify() for n in phi["neutral"]]
467            formula.update([(~f | p).simplify() for p in all_phi_pos])
468            formula.update([(f | n).simplify() for n in all_phi_neg])
469            formula.update([n for n in all_phi_neut])
470        # add the validity constraints
471        formula.update(validity_constraints)
472        # create CNF formula
473        full_formula = And({*[f.simplify() for f in formula]}).simplify()
474        cnf_formula = And(map(SLAF.__or_refactor, full_formula.children))
475
476        entailed = set()
477        if sample:
478            with config(sat_backend="kissat"):
479                sol = cnf_formula.solve()
480                if sol:
481                    for f in all_var:
482                        if sol[str(f)]:
483                            entailed.add(f)
484        else:
485            children = set(cnf_formula.children)
486            # iterate through all fluents, gathering those that are entailed
487            for f in all_var:
488                children.add(Or([~f]))
489                check_theory = And(children)
490                # if False, then f is entailed
491                with config(sat_backend="kissat"):
492                    if not check_theory.solve():
493                        entailed.add(f)
494                children.discard(Or([~f]))
495        return entailed

SLAF model extraction method.

Amir, E, and A Chang. 2008. “Learning Partially Observable Deterministic Action Models.” Journal of Artificial Intelligence Research 33: 349–402. https://doi.org/10.1613/jair.2575.

Extracts a Model from state observations using the SLAF technique. The AS-STRIPS-SLAF algorithm is used to extract the effects of actions given a trace/observation. The algorithm is incapable of finding the preconditions of those actions, however.

Note that SLAF learns partially observable, deterministic action models, and thus takes PartialObservation as the token type.

The AS-STRIPS-SLAF algorithm works by defining "action propositions" for each action that define the possible preconditions, effects, or lack-thereof of that action and every possible fluent. A propositional formula is updated as each step is iterated through, and kept in a "fluent-factored form" that specifies the possible "explanations" behind each fluent being true, false, or unaffected. As actions are taken and states observed, these reasonings are updated and simplified. (Note that the pieces of the formula are stored carefully so as to easily conjoin them into one CNF formula later). Once all steps in the trace have been iterated through, the CNF formula is created, and all possible fluents/action propositions are iterated through to determine which ones are entailed. This information is then used to extract the Model.

class Observer: 
 22class Observer:
 23    """Observer model extraction method.
 24
 25    Extracts a Model from state observations using the observer technique.  All
 26    the fluents present in the observations are saved as is. The actions have
 27    their preconditions, add effects, and delete effects found and added to the
 28    object.
 29
 30    The preconditions of an action are defined as the (positive) intersection
 31    of all pre-states to that action. The effects are the union off all fluents
 32    that changed state from a pre-state to a post-state of an action. Add this
 33    effects are fluents that went from False to True, delete effects are
 34    fluents that went from True to False.
 35    """
 36
 37    def __new__(cls, obs_tracelist: ObservedTraceList, **kwargs):
 38        """Creates a new Model object.
 39
 40        Args:
 41            observations (ObservationList):
 42                The state observations to extract the model from.
 43        Raises:
 44            IncompatibleObservationToken:
 45                Raised if the observations are not identity observation.
 46        """
 47        if obs_tracelist.type is not IdentityObservation:
 48            raise IncompatibleObservationToken(obs_tracelist.type, Observer)
 49        fluents = Observer._get_fluents(obs_tracelist)
 50        actions = Observer._get_actions(obs_tracelist)
 51        return Model(fluents, actions)
 52
 53    @staticmethod
 54    def _get_fluents(obs_tracelist: ObservedTraceList):
 55        """Retrieves the set of fluents in the observations."""
 56        fluents = set()
 57        obs_trace: List[IdentityObservation]
 58        for obs_trace in obs_tracelist:
 59            for obs in obs_trace:
 60                # Update fluents with the fluents in this observation
 61                fluents.update(
 62                    LearnedFluent(f.name, [o.details() for o in f.objects])
 63                    for f in obs.state.keys()
 64                )
 65        return fluents
 66
 67    @staticmethod
 68    def _get_actions(obs_tracelist: ObservedTraceList):
 69        """Retrieves and augments the set of actions in the observations."""
 70        # Get the unique actions and the relevant traces
 71        action_obs = defaultdict(list)
 72        obs_trace: List[IdentityObservation]
 73        for obs_trace in obs_tracelist:
 74            for obs in obs_trace:
 75                action = obs.action
 76                if action:  # Final step has no action
 77                    action_obs[action].append(obs_trace)
 78
 79        action_pre_states = defaultdict(set)
 80        # Get transitions for each action
 81        action_transitions = obs_tracelist.get_all_transitions()
 82        for action, transitions in action_transitions.items():
 83            # Create a LearnedAction for the current action
 84            model_action = LearnedAction(
 85                action.name, action.obj_params, cost=action.cost
 86            )
 87
 88            for pre, post in transitions:
 89                # Add all action pre-states to a set
 90                action_pre_states[model_action].add(pre.state)
 91                # Update the action's effects
 92                delta = Observer.get_delta(pre.state, post.state)
 93                model_action.update_add({str(f) for f in delta.added})
 94                model_action.update_delete({str(f) for f in delta.deleted})
 95
 96        for action, pre_states in action_pre_states.items():
 97            # Find the (positive) intersection of the pre-states
 98            precond = set.intersection(*map(Observer._filter_positive, pre_states))
 99            action.update_precond({str(f) for f in precond})
100
101        return {action for action in action_pre_states}
102
103    @staticmethod
104    def get_delta(pre: dict, post: dict):
105        """Determines the delta-state between pre and post.
106
107        Args:
108            pre (dict):
109                The pre-state to compare.
110            post (dict):
111                The post-state to compare.
112
113        Returns:
114            A `DeltaState` object, containing two sets: `added` and `deleted`.
115            The added set contains the list of fluents that were False in this
116            state and True in `other`. The deleted set contains the list of
117            fluents that were True in this state and False in `other`.
118        """
119        added = set()
120        deleted = set()
121        for f in pre:
122            if pre[f] and not post[f]:  # true pre, false post -> deleted
123                deleted.add(f)
124            elif not pre[f] and post[f]:  # false pre, true post -> added
125                added.add(f)
126        return DeltaObservation(added, deleted)
127
128    @staticmethod
129    def _filter_positive(state):
130        """Returns the set of true fluents in a state."""
131        true_fluents = set()
132        for fluent, is_true in state.items():
133            if is_true:
134                true_fluents.add(fluent)
135        return true_fluents

Observer model extraction method.

Extracts a Model from state observations using the observer technique. All the fluents present in the observations are saved as is. The actions have their preconditions, add effects, and delete effects found and added to the object.

The preconditions of an action are defined as the (positive) intersection of all pre-states to that action. The effects are the union off all fluents that changed state from a pre-state to a post-state of an action. Add this effects are fluents that went from False to True, delete effects are fluents that went from True to False.

103    @staticmethod
104    def get_delta(pre: dict, post: dict):
105        """Determines the delta-state between pre and post.
106
107        Args:
108            pre (dict):
109                The pre-state to compare.
110            post (dict):
111                The post-state to compare.
112
113        Returns:
114            A `DeltaState` object, containing two sets: `added` and `deleted`.
115            The added set contains the list of fluents that were False in this
116            state and True in `other`. The deleted set contains the list of
117            fluents that were True in this state and False in `other`.
118        """
119        added = set()
120        deleted = set()
121        for f in pre:
122            if pre[f] and not post[f]:  # true pre, false post -> deleted
123                deleted.add(f)
124            elif not pre[f] and post[f]:  # false pre, true post -> added
125                added.add(f)
126        return DeltaObservation(added, deleted)
